title: Italian restaurant Branca going into Tower280 at Midtown
text:
Tower280, the new name for the renovated Midtown Tower building, will soon have an Italian restaurant inside. Branca Italian Restaurant will open its second location inside Tower280, the building's developers announced Monday. Buckingham Properties and Morgan Management said the restaurant will occupy 4,500 square feet. Branca already has its main location in Bushnell's Basin.
Branca is Tower280's first retail occupant. The developers are devoting nearly 50,000 square feet to retail inside the building, which will also house offices and residential units.
The developers are planning 181 apartments and two floors for office space. Architectural and engineering firm Bergmann Associates will occupy one of the floors .
